README.md:80:Chrome, Arc, Brave, Edge, and other Chromium browsers may ask for browser Safe Storage Keychain access so Pinemeter can decrypt cookies. Safari cookies are protected by macOS and may require Full Disk Access.
README.md:206:- Session keys are stored securely in macOS Keychain (encrypted, device-local only)
README.md:207:- Browser import reads local browser cookies to extract your Claude session, then stores only the session key in Keychain
README.md:208:- Usage data is cached locally (unencrypted, contains usage percentages only)
CHANGELOG.md:89:- Export usage data to ~/.claudemeter/usage.json for external tools
CHANGELOG.md:147:- Initial ClaudeMeter macOS menu bar app
